cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the problem of processing gigapixel whole slide images (WSIs) in clinical microscopy, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the selective use of high resolution processing based on the confidence of predictions on downscaled WSIs, which is a machine learning approach (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of modern computing resources, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
